==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[vicarius|vicārius]]'' "vicarious, substitute"

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪkə(r)|-ɪkə(r)]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# In the [[Church of England]], the [[priest]] of a [[parish]], receiving a [[salary]] or [[stipend]] but not [[tithes]].
# In the [[Roman Catholic]] and some other [[church]]es, a [[cleric]] acting as [[local]] [[representative]] of a [[higher]] [[ranking]] member of the [[clergy]].

